<br>
I always thought SDPS is the DPS at which mana regen equals mana consumption, therefore can be sustained indefinitely (or as least for hours, like in XP groups).  Am I wrong?  I see people quoting these &quot;sustainable&quot; DPS number on 1 boss-mob fight.  I understand the calc and I understand you can use that to compare damage output against melees in a one-fight situation but those are not sustainable by any means, right?  Isn't that Max DPS?  Not SDPS?  Or am I just not understanding it?<br>
<br>
In my mind, SDPS balanced:<br>
<br>
Mana Consumption over time = mana usage based on spells - mana preservation, taking into account of cast time with focus effect (like Spell Haste)<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
Mana Regen over time = mana regen based on innate, flappy, buffs, FT gear, etc. + Harvests<br>
<br>
from that balance, the specific spell damage is used to calculate SDPS.<br>
<br>
So SDPS is character dependent, level dependent, AA dependent, buff dependent, focus dependent, and spell dependent.  As in, a level x with these focuses and these buffs using this spell will have a SDPS of n.  e.g. A level 65 with SCF3 + SCM3 + HoD, horse, GFlappy, Force Shield, C3, SP, Pot9, and FT10, will have a SDPS of nnn when using SoS and a SDPS of mmm when using ISoS.  Am I wrong? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tanizwyntertop>Taniz Wyntertop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 4:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizzy's DPS</span><hr size=1> After Luclin, Wizards were more or less balanced against melees. With PoP, they FINALLY got it right, they boosted casting classes fairly compared to the melee classes. <br>
